==English==
===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /beɪl/

===Etymology 1===
Probably from Middle Dutch ''bale'' (Dutch [[baal]]).

====Noun====
'''bale'''
#A bundle or package of goods in a cloth cover, and corded for storage or transportation; also, a bundle of straw / hay, etc., put up compactly for transportation.
#A measurement of hay equal to 10 flakes.  Approximately 70-90 lbs.
====Verb====
'''to bale''' ('''[[bales]]''', '''[[baled]]''', '''[[baling]]''')
#''(transitive)'' to [[wrap]] in a bale

===Etymology 2===
Old English [[bealo]].

====Noun====
'''bale'''
#[[evil]]
====Derived terms====
*[[baleful]]


